I would start by making sure your HTML is valid. Attributes like `style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;` won&#39;t work if the elements they&#39;re being applied to aren&#39;t formed correctly.

Also your `&lt;li&gt;`&#39;s are List Items and they need to be part of a list. Lists can be an ordered list `ol` (List Items will be numbered) or an unordered list `ul` (List Items will just be bullet points), the choice is yours, but either way List Items have to be included in a list first:

Use an unordered list
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;when&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;order&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;doesn&#39;t&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;matter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

And an ordered list
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;when&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;it&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;does&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

And you have a couple `&lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;`&#39;s in there, those should be your List Items (`li`&#39;s). So instead of:

`&lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Long Sleeves&lt;/div&gt;` 

I would change that to:

`&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Long Sleeves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;`

